The Perimeter Layer protects network boundaries from external threats.

Controls include:

* Firewalls
* DDoS protection
* Web Application Firewalls

For example, Azure DDoS Protection defends against traffic floods.

# Real-Life Use Case:
A real-life use case is protecting public-facing websites.

# Real-Life Example:
Another example is filtering malicious internet traffic.

Perimeter security helps block threats before they enter internal systems.
